WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:15.130 --> 00:00:20.200
Germa 66 once conquered
the North Blue by force.

3
00:00:21.170 --> 00:00:27.790
The six Vinsmokes at the top
will be riddled with bullets tomorrow.

4
00:00:27.790 --> 00:00:29.130
The wedding ceremony will be...

5
00:00:29.950 --> 00:00:32.400
dyed red with blood.

6
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:33.630
Bang.

7
00:00:38.660 --> 00:00:42.170
But even when you're dying,

8
00:00:42.170 --> 00:00:46.660
please try not to get your blood everywhere.
And don't scream out, either.

9
00:00:46.660 --> 00:00:49.540
You have to be careful.

10
00:00:49.540 --> 00:00:53.990
If the wedding cake gets
splattered with blood, Mama will be furious,

11
00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:56.570
and she'll destroy the building.

12
00:01:00.530 --> 00:01:05.580
This is a .36 caliber Walker percussion pistol.

13
00:01:05.580 --> 00:01:08.950
It fires bullets called candy jackets.

14
00:01:08.950 --> 00:01:13.880
They're powerful enough to pierce through armored soldiers.

15
00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:16.380
But you've already witnessed its power firsthand, right?

16
00:01:18.550 --> 00:01:22.100
These bullets will be able to penetrate
all of your metal-enhanced bodies.

17
00:01:27.730 --> 00:01:29.740
I can't wait for tomorrow!

18
00:01:29.740 --> 00:01:35.950
I want to see Sanji's face when I,
the one he trusts, points a gun at his head.

19
00:01:37.860 --> 00:01:40.830
I can't wait to see that!

20
00:01:38.160 --> 00:01:45.710
The Jelly

21
00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:45.710
The Carpet

22
00:01:40.830 --> 00:01:45.410
He truly believes that you love him!

23
00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:51.540
It'll be something to see.

24
00:01:55.260 --> 00:01:58.300
What will his face look like?

25
00:01:58.300 --> 00:02:03.000
Let's see... Maybe it'll look like this?

26
00:02:04.220 --> 00:02:06.890
That's perfect!

27
00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:06.890
You're so funny!

28
00:02:10.230 --> 00:02:13.350
Or maybe like this?

29
00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:16.360
P-Pudding-chan...

30
00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:24.370
What's wrong?
You aren't paying attention.

31
00:02:24.990 --> 00:02:28.210
We're talking about your brother.

32
00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:31.780
She's right. Why don't you listen?

33
00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:33.590
Listen!

34
00:02:33.590 --> 00:02:37.440
Do you want to know how he proposed to me?

35
00:02:40.010 --> 00:02:42.920
Oh! It was perfect!

36
00:02:42.920 --> 00:02:47.290
When he pulled off the face pack,
he looked terrible.

37
00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:52.860
But I was waiting for that exact moment.

38
00:02:52.860 --> 00:02:55.990
By showing tears right there,

39
00:02:55.990 --> 00:02:57.550
I won his heart.

40
00:02:57.550 --> 00:03:02.030
I won't let your marriage with me be hell!

41
00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:07.460
Seriously, men are dumb.

42
00:03:21.130 --> 00:03:26.160
Then that idiot pulled me
into his arms right then and there,

43
00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:30.790
and said in a quiet whisper,

44
00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:41.450
"You're my salvation.
Let's get married."

45
00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:43.280
"Let's get married."

46
00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:45.570
"Let's get married!"

47
00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:49.620
"Let's get married!"

48
00:03:49.620 --> 00:03:52.630
Stop it! I can't breathe!

49
00:03:53.870 --> 00:03:54.790
Hey.

50
00:03:54.790 --> 00:03:59.370
That's such a pathetic proposal,
don't you think?!

51
00:04:06.170 --> 00:04:08.560
Oh, it was so funny!

52
00:04:08.560 --> 00:04:14.610
Who in the world would marry a failure like him?!

53
00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:27.600
Couldn't it at least have been a proper prince?

54
00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:37.230
Sanji!

55
00:06:56.600 --> 00:07:04.150
<b>Germa's Failure</b>

56
00:07:05.100 --> 00:07:09.190
Are you still trying to get up?

57
00:07:06.060 --> 00:07:09.700
<b>Treasure
Repository</b>

58
00:07:10.080 --> 00:07:11.930
Yes, I am.

59
00:07:14.650 --> 00:07:19.410
Why? Why do you want to keep standing, Soul King?

60
00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:24.780
Is it because of the stone, Soul King?

61
00:07:24.780 --> 00:07:29.800
Is that more important to you than rescuing Sanji?

62
00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:31.420
Yes.

63
00:07:33.590 --> 00:07:37.790
Sanji-san is a kind man.

64
00:07:38.760 --> 00:07:43.920
That's why I figured he'd never come back.

65
00:07:43.920 --> 00:07:47.810
I don't know what kind of
trap you set for him...

66
00:07:49.690 --> 00:07:53.220
but he's an extremely kind man,

67
00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:58.700
so once he's made up his mind to sacrifice himself
for someone, he will not change his mind!

68
00:07:58.700 --> 00:08:04.340
And our captain, at the same time, is someone who
always trusts his own beliefs when he acts!

69
00:08:04.340 --> 00:08:08.980
That's why those two young men
will decide what happens here!

70
00:08:12.170 --> 00:08:14.200
I see!

71
00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:18.840
So you have nothing better to do
than come for the stone?

72
00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:25.300
No, I am doing it so that if, in the worst-case scenario,
Sanji-san does not return with us,

73
00:08:25.300 --> 00:08:27.560
he will not blame himself for bringing us here!

74
00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:35.070
I want him to know that
this rescue mission was still beneficial!

75
00:08:35.780 --> 00:08:39.600
So I must get it! The lode poneglyph!

76
00:08:42.410 --> 00:08:46.830
Your worst-case scenario is too tame.

77
00:08:46.830 --> 00:08:51.300
Sanji not returning? Is that really the worst that could happen?

78
00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:53.950
I don't think it is.

79
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:57.080
Do you think nobody's gonna die?

80
00:08:57.080 --> 00:09:00.100
Maybe all of you will die!

81
00:09:00.100 --> 00:09:06.300
What kind of fool draws up plans
with the expectation of death, young lady?

82
00:09:11.140 --> 00:09:16.180
<b>Mirro-world</b>

83
00:09:18.520 --> 00:09:21.110
St... St... Stop!

84
00:09:21.110 --> 00:09:23.860
Okay! Tickle, tickle, tickle!

85
00:09:26.070 --> 00:09:28.400
Tell us already!

86
00:09:28.400 --> 00:09:32.240
Carrot's special tickle, tickle, tickle!

87
00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:34.610
Stop!

88
00:09:35.330 --> 00:09:37.170
Stop tickling me!

89
00:09:37.170 --> 00:09:41.290
Just say it! If you don't,
she'll tickle you forever!

90
00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:43.130
I'll say it! I'll say it!

91
00:09:43.130 --> 00:09:45.220
Okay, Carrot, stop.

92
00:09:45.220 --> 00:09:47.180
Okay.

93
00:09:50.850 --> 00:09:53.610
I'll make you pay for this!

94
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:57.280
Answer our question.
Which mirror leads to the castle?

95
00:09:57.280 --> 00:10:01.190
I don't remember every single mirror!

96
00:10:01.190 --> 00:10:04.240
That's not the right answer!

97
00:10:04.240 --> 00:10:07.040
You have to ask the mirrors!

98
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:10.210
Huh? The mirrors?

99
00:10:09.210 --> 00:10:10.210
Ask?

100
00:10:10.210 --> 00:10:15.920
That's right! The mirrors all know what they're reflecting!

101
00:10:15.920 --> 00:10:17.210
What?

102
00:10:24.600 --> 00:10:26.680
Mirror, mirror!

103
00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:29.600
Which one of you is a mirror to the castle?!

104
00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:30.810
I am!

105
00:10:30.810 --> 00:10:31.790
Me!

106
00:10:31.790 --> 00:10:34.780
It's me.

107
00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:34.780
Me too.

108
00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:38.030
They answered!

109
00:10:38.030 --> 00:10:40.360
Here! Me too!

110
00:10:39.660 --> 00:10:40.360
Me too!

111
00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:41.490
Me too!

112
00:10:41.490 --> 00:10:44.770
I'm the mirror in Mistress Galette's closet.

113
00:10:44.770 --> 00:10:48.300
I'm a hand mirror in a guest room
on the second floor.

114
00:10:48.300 --> 00:10:50.670
I'm a mirror in the ladies' room
on the fourth floor.

115
00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:56.050
Do any of you currently reflect
Luffy, Nami, Brook, Pedro, or Sanji?

116
00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:57.920
We're looking for them!

117
00:10:57.920 --> 00:10:59.170
Who?

118
00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:00.630
What do they look like?

119
00:11:00.630 --> 00:11:03.070
Prince Sanji passed by earlier.

120
00:11:03.780 --> 00:11:07.210
Oh, yeah. They don't know
what they look like.

121
00:11:07.210 --> 00:11:10.430
Count on me, Chobro!
I'm good at drawing!

122
00:11:10.430 --> 00:11:12.520
What? Drawing?

123
00:11:12.520 --> 00:11:14.790
Uh-huh!

124
00:11:18.490 --> 00:11:21.730
You're so unfortunate to have
such a dumb brother.

125
00:11:21.730 --> 00:11:24.820
Yeah, you really are!

126
00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.700
If we leave her like this,
she'll be dead before the morning.

127
00:11:28.740 --> 00:11:33.870
We can't let that happen.
That'll ruin our whole plan.

128
00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:39.710
We need her to live until tomorrow.

129
00:11:51.550 --> 00:11:54.400
Now, Big Sister.

130
00:11:56.680 --> 00:11:59.450
It'll give us trouble if you die like this.

131
00:11:59.450 --> 00:12:02.440
And it'll give us trouble
if you reveal my ungraceful nature,

132
00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:04.740
as you've just seen.

133
00:12:19.090 --> 00:12:20.920
What are you...?

134
00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:24.000
Stay calm. It won't take long.

135
00:12:59.540 --> 00:13:02.770
This is the power of the Memo-Memo Fruit.

136
00:13:02.770 --> 00:13:07.130
Everyone has a roll of film in their head
that records memories.

137
00:13:07.130 --> 00:13:10.870
You have scary experiences, sad memories,

138
00:13:10.870 --> 00:13:14.270
and things that you want to forget, don't you?

139
00:13:15.520 --> 00:13:19.150
I'm impressed with Germa 66.

140
00:13:19.150 --> 00:13:22.730
You were shot in the leg,
but you still made it that far.

141
00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:24.580
You're uselessly tough!

142
00:13:27.730 --> 00:13:29.980
She's right!

143
00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:33.970
Now, I'll paste a memory strip

144
00:13:33.970 --> 00:13:37.620
from one of the soldiers who was shot
by a stray bullet here and...

145
00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:39.150
Edit!

146
00:13:43.710 --> 00:13:45.500
All done!

147
00:13:47.060 --> 00:13:50.510
Your most recent memories
involving me have been cut.

148
00:13:50.510 --> 00:13:53.430
Let's have a joyous wedding tomorrow.

149
00:13:53.870 --> 00:13:56.560
Call the soldiers to escort her
to the medical room.

150
00:13:56.560 --> 00:13:58.010
Okay.

151
00:13:58.010 --> 00:14:01.210
<b>Prisoner Library</b>

152
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:04.140
Stop! No!

153
00:14:12.450 --> 00:14:16.610
Seriously, stop it, Luffy!
You're scaring me! That's enough!

154
00:14:22.330 --> 00:14:25.540
Stop it!
Your arms really will be torn apart!

155
00:14:25.540 --> 00:14:30.550
I don't care!
I gotta tell Sanji about Pudding!

156
00:14:30.550 --> 00:14:32.500
That rat!

157
00:14:36.760 --> 00:14:40.680
No! I said don't do it! Luffy!

158
00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:44.230
Ow, ow, ow... A little more to go!

159
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:48.830
He's so reckless.
Hey, girl.

160
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:51.190
What?! I'm busy now!

161
00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:56.650
Mama ordered me to get Lola's whereabouts
out of you during the night.

162
00:14:56.650 --> 00:14:58.440
So just tell me now.

163
00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:01.280
No! I'm not going to sell out my friend!

164
00:15:01.280 --> 00:15:03.490
Okay, then. I'm gonna torture you.

165
00:15:03.490 --> 00:15:05.640
No! Don't say that so casually!

166
00:15:07.290 --> 00:15:11.750
Alright, I'm gonna shoot you with a crossbow
once every five seconds,

167
00:15:11.750 --> 00:15:14.000
so just tell me whenever you're ready.

168
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:16.260
What? What do you mean?

169
00:15:16.260 --> 00:15:18.070
Don't do that... It'll kill me!

170
00:15:18.070 --> 00:15:19.770
Then just tell me.

171
00:15:19.770 --> 00:15:22.780
Screw you, wart head!
I won't let you do that!

172
00:15:22.780 --> 00:15:26.010
It's gonna be okay, Nami!
I'll rip my arms off in the next five seconds!

173
00:15:26.010 --> 00:15:27.230
What?!

174
00:15:27.230 --> 00:15:29.980
No! I don't want either of those to happen!

175
00:15:29.980 --> 00:15:31.200
Don't be a baby!

176
00:15:32.150 --> 00:15:35.080
Hey! Is anybody here?!

177
00:15:36.820 --> 00:15:41.820
Oh! Whoa! Whoa! I thought you weren't
allowed to enter the castle now!

178
00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:46.450
Don't be so hardheaded.
There is chaos all over this castle.

179
00:15:47.870 --> 00:15:49.710
Sorry to do this, Opera...

180
00:15:52.440 --> 00:15:55.130
Five Thousand Tile...

181
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:55.130
What?!

182
00:15:56.250 --> 00:15:57.990
Fist!

183
00:16:28.620 --> 00:16:32.670
Sorry. Why don't you sleep for a while?

184
00:16:33.590 --> 00:16:35.510
Jinbe!

185
00:16:35.510 --> 00:16:37.870
Oh, Luffy! Nami!

186
00:16:37.870 --> 00:16:40.380
Why are you here?!

187
00:16:40.900 --> 00:16:45.220
I heard you got caught.
I'm glad that you're okay.

188
00:16:45.220 --> 00:16:47.470
We can talk later.

189
00:16:47.470 --> 00:16:50.390
But first, don't you want to get out of there?

190
00:16:50.390 --> 00:16:52.390
We do!

191
00:16:52.390 --> 00:16:56.590
<b>Whole Cake Chateau</b>

192
00:16:56.690 --> 00:16:58.880
<b>Medical Room</b>

193
00:16:58.870 --> 00:17:04.330
She was bleeding badly,
but the wound has already started healing.

194
00:17:04.330 --> 00:17:07.790
What incredibly resilient and regenerative skin.

195
00:17:08.410 --> 00:17:12.170
This is the true power of Germa's modified humans.

196
00:17:12.170 --> 00:17:17.750
If she stays in bed for the night, she should be able to attend the tea party tomorrow.

197
00:17:21.260 --> 00:17:25.090
Guard her for the rest of the night.

198
00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:28.760
Don't forget to tell the Vinsmokes about this.

199
00:17:28.760 --> 00:17:30.850
I'm sure they're worried about her.

200
00:17:30.850 --> 00:17:31.950
Yes, sir.

201
00:17:31.950 --> 00:17:35.940
Anyway, I'll be in the medical office
on the fourth floor.

202
00:17:35.940 --> 00:17:42.150
I don't have time to sleep with the amount
of wounded people that are in the castle right now.

203
00:17:42.150 --> 00:17:45.080
Thank you for your service. Take care.

204
00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:05.230
Where am I?

205
00:18:10.810 --> 00:18:11.940
Sanji!

206
00:18:14.190 --> 00:18:16.390
I hurt my leg...

207
00:18:17.150 --> 00:18:20.190
Do you remember how that happened?

208
00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:25.610
I was walking around the castle,

209
00:18:25.610 --> 00:18:29.490
and then I ran across soldiers
who were going after intruders...

210
00:18:30.080 --> 00:18:32.920
and I got attacked, I suppose?

211
00:18:32.920 --> 00:18:36.540
That doesn't make sense, does it?
Of course not.

212
00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:38.830
Your memories were replaced.

213
00:18:38.830 --> 00:18:39.420
What?

214
00:18:39.420 --> 00:18:44.710
I'll tell you what really happened.

215
00:18:47.090 --> 00:18:50.290
<b>Prisoner Library</b>

216
00:18:50.270 --> 00:18:53.720
Books can be destroyed by fire.

217
00:18:53.720 --> 00:18:57.230
Are you gonna burn the cage?
Is that a good idea?

218
00:18:57.230 --> 00:19:02.020
Yes, but only if you two can get out of there before burning up.

219
00:19:02.020 --> 00:19:04.690
Alright. Do it!

220
00:19:03.660 --> 00:19:04.690
That quick?!

221
00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:07.400
No, I'm still not ready!

222
00:19:09.200 --> 00:19:12.030
We're really gonna burn!

223
00:19:12.030 --> 00:19:14.620
Burn it up already!

224
00:19:15.250 --> 00:19:16.450
Alright!

225
00:19:20.750 --> 00:19:21.880
Ouch!

226
00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:24.170
Hurry up! Luffy! Nami!

227
00:19:39.940 --> 00:19:43.110
We got out!

228
00:19:45.490 --> 00:19:50.610
I feel like I've been through
something like this before...

229
00:19:50.610 --> 00:19:53.830
I'm sorry, both of you.

230
00:19:55.080 --> 00:19:58.790
Thanks to you,
I didn't have to rip my arms apart!

231
00:19:58.790 --> 00:20:02.670
Come to think of it, we met each other...

232
00:20:03.170 --> 00:20:06.130
in a prison like this.

233
00:20:07.010 --> 00:20:12.670
Look! These people were all inside that book.

234
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:16.890
The imagination and span
of the World of Books is infinite.

235
00:20:16.890 --> 00:20:22.230
Big Mom has many powerful followers
just like Mont d'Or.

236
00:20:26.860 --> 00:20:31.200
Thank you, Jinbe!
But why are you here?

237
00:20:32.130 --> 00:20:38.700
My Sun Pirates are also
affiliated with Big Mom.

238
00:20:38.700 --> 00:20:40.620
What?!

239
00:20:40.620 --> 00:20:42.950
Oh, but...

240
00:20:42.950 --> 00:20:45.250
that means this is...

241
00:20:45.670 --> 00:20:50.170
Yes, this is a rebellion.
There's no turning back now!

242
00:20:51.130 --> 00:20:52.450
What? Is that okay?

243
00:20:52.450 --> 00:20:56.360
On Fishman Island,
you said that you had other obligations.

244
00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:58.320
I just took care of them.

245
00:20:58.320 --> 00:21:01.470
Someone heard screams
from the Prisoner Library!

246
00:21:01.470 --> 00:21:03.480
What's going on?!

247
00:21:02.880 --> 00:21:04.430
Ugh, they've already noticed!

248
00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:06.620
They're indeed quick.

249
00:21:06.620 --> 00:21:10.990
First, we have to hide
in a place where they can't find us.

250
00:21:10.990 --> 00:21:13.890
– Yeah.
– Let's go, then!

251
00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:19.160
All of a sudden... I feel hungry.

252
00:21:19.160 --> 00:21:21.510
You're hungry at a time like this?

253
00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:26.670
Luffy expends three times the energy
of a normal person when he does something.

254
00:21:26.670 --> 00:21:32.030
It's okay. I'm not saying
that I wanna eat something.

255
00:21:33.720 --> 00:21:36.700
Your stomach is growling.

256
00:21:36.700 --> 00:21:38.510
Never mind!

257
00:21:38.510 --> 00:21:43.690
I won't eat anything
other than what you cook!

258
00:21:43.690 --> 00:21:47.710
Even if I get hungry
or spears rain down on me,

259
00:21:47.710 --> 00:21:52.570
I'll stay right here and wait for you!

260
00:21:52.570 --> 00:21:55.490
Anyway, Jinbe, thank you!

261
00:21:57.600 --> 00:22:00.600
I actually...

262
00:22:00.600 --> 00:22:05.820
was proposed to by Sanji-san.

263
00:22:05.820 --> 00:22:09.320
I'm not going to marry him, because...

264
00:22:09.320 --> 00:22:14.300
he's an idiot that played right into my hands by falling for me...

265
00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:17.100
and because he's going to be shot in the middle of the ceremony...

266
00:22:17.100 --> 00:22:19.980
by me.

267
00:22:19.980 --> 00:22:22.210
Things can't get any worse!

268
00:22:22.210 --> 00:22:27.100
We were all fooled! Sanji too!
I gotta let him know!

269
00:22:27.100 --> 00:22:29.820
Take care of Nami, Jinbe!

270
00:22:29.820 --> 00:22:33.700
Luffy, wait!
There are tons of tough enemies in the castle!

271
00:22:33.700 --> 00:22:38.740
And you're not fully recovered!
Don't you remember what happened this morning?!

272
00:22:38.740 --> 00:22:41.730
I'm not gonna be defeated this time!

273
00:22:55.390 --> 00:22:58.890
<b>Medical Room</b>

274
00:22:58.940 --> 00:23:00.400
Do you believe me?

275
00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:05.300
Of course, I do.
I know you wouldn't lie to me.

276
00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:09.770
But I didn't realize
Pudding's true character was this heinous.

277
00:23:09.770 --> 00:23:11.790
I wasn't completely sure.

278
00:23:11.790 --> 00:23:15.250
But I thought she seemed a little too perfect,

279
00:23:15.250 --> 00:23:17.790
so I was spying on her myself.

280
00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:23.470
If she wasn't planning to marry me from the start,
and if the plan was to kill us all along,

281
00:23:23.470 --> 00:23:29.360
then the promise I was given that Luffy and the others would be safe...

282
00:23:29.360 --> 00:23:33.380
was just a big lie!

283
00:23:33.380 --> 00:23:38.250
I thought I could sacrifice myself,
and everything would be fine!

284
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:44.260
But that was nothing but false hope!
How could I have been so naive?

285
00:23:44.260 --> 00:23:49.520
Our father may be smart,
but even he was careless in this situation.

286
00:23:49.520 --> 00:23:55.940
He's dealing with an emperor.
He should've been more careful.

287
00:23:55.940 --> 00:23:59.700
But this is a good situation, in my opinion.

288
00:23:59.700 --> 00:24:02.810
I believe that Germa should be destroyed.

289
00:24:03.830 --> 00:24:07.060
I'll just pretend I know nothing,

290
00:24:07.060 --> 00:24:09.700
and let Big Mom's plan be carried out...

291
00:24:09.700 --> 00:24:14.040
What are you talking about?
If you go to the tea party, they'll kill you too, Reiju!

292
00:24:14.040 --> 00:24:17.840
Oh, are you worried about me?

293
00:24:21.430 --> 00:24:24.880
This is the problem with old memories.

294
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:28.520
You don't need to think that you're indebted
to me for helping you that one time.

295
00:24:29.980 --> 00:24:33.520
Leave this island with the Straw Hats, Sanji.

296
00:24:33.520 --> 00:24:37.980
Huh?! I can't do that!
If I do that, what will happen to the Baratie?

297
00:24:37.980 --> 00:24:41.440
You can worry about that after you've escaped.

298
00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:43.800
If you stay here, everybody will die.

299
00:24:43.800 --> 00:24:48.240
Sanji, you can't die.
For our mother's sake!

300
00:24:48.240 --> 00:24:49.670
What do you mean?

301
00:24:50.140 --> 00:24:55.130
I have a memory that I will never forget.

302
00:25:02.550 --> 00:25:05.760
What are you talking about?

303
00:25:06.490 --> 00:25:09.120
Mother and Father had a big fight.

304
00:25:09.120 --> 00:25:11.270
It happened when I was a child.

305
00:25:11.270 --> 00:25:16.480
I always wondered why
our sweet mother was so angry.

306
00:25:16.480 --> 00:25:19.860
But it made sense much later.

307
00:25:20.820 --> 00:25:24.420
When our mother was pregnant with you four,

308
00:25:24.420 --> 00:25:30.260
she was strongly against turning you
into emotionless machines.

309
00:25:30.750 --> 00:25:33.260
– Are you serious?!
– Of course I am!

310
00:25:33.260 --> 00:25:36.270
How can you want to do such a horrible thing?

311
00:25:36.270 --> 00:25:39.130
The operating room is ready.

312
00:25:39.130 --> 00:25:42.190
Don't do this! They're my children, too!

313
00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:46.010
If you get rid of their emotions, they won't be human anymore!

314
00:25:46.010 --> 00:25:50.060
I want them to be monsters.
Winning wars is all that matters.

315
00:25:51.850 --> 00:25:57.250
The reestablishment of the Vinsmoke family
that once conquered the North Blue.

316
00:25:57.250 --> 00:26:01.040
Accomplishing that goal... requires strength.

317
00:26:01.040 --> 00:26:04.870
I'll give my children the greatest power possible!

318
00:26:05.780 --> 00:26:07.860
– No!
– Take her!

319
00:26:07.860 --> 00:26:10.050
What are you...? No! Let go of me!

320
00:26:10.050 --> 00:26:13.200
Dear! Don't do it!
They're my children!

321
00:26:13.200 --> 00:26:14.290
No!

322
00:26:15.030 --> 00:26:17.960
Then they performed the surgery.

323
00:26:20.710 --> 00:26:28.250
But our mother took a powerful drug
to try and foil our father's plan.

324
00:26:43.860 --> 00:26:46.380
Hey, what have you done, Sora?

325
00:26:46.380 --> 00:26:51.370
This drug was strong enough to affect
the manipulated hereditary elements.

326
00:26:54.160 --> 00:26:57.080
But her actions weren't enough.

327
00:26:59.330 --> 00:27:05.380
They soon found superhuman abnormalities
in our brothers' bodies.

328
00:27:05.380 --> 00:27:07.130
I can't believe it!

329
00:27:10.550 --> 00:27:13.430
The surgery was a success.

330
00:27:12.690 --> 00:27:13.430
Great!

331
00:27:13.430 --> 00:27:19.710
Don't worry! Their genetic blueprints
won't be affected by some drug.

332
00:27:28.750 --> 00:27:30.710
Let's play!

333
00:27:30.710 --> 00:27:34.930
But it's strange.
Only Prince Sanji is...

334
00:27:34.930 --> 00:27:40.100
That can't be right.
Let's watch over his growth.

335
00:27:55.220 --> 00:27:59.280
Are you hungry? Hold on.

336
00:27:59.280 --> 00:28:00.480
Here.

337
00:28:01.650 --> 00:28:03.240
Is it good?

338
00:28:05.070 --> 00:28:08.020
Prince Sanji is feeding birds!

339
00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:10.570
He mustn't have those kinds of emotions!

340
00:28:10.570 --> 00:28:12.030
Sora!

341
00:28:12.750 --> 00:28:16.920
As you grew up, you kept acting human.

342
00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:21.420
Meanwhile, our mother
grew weaker and weaker,

343
00:28:21.420 --> 00:28:23.720
because of the drug she took.

344
00:28:24.260 --> 00:28:27.270
Then... she died because of me?!

345
00:28:27.270 --> 00:28:29.210
Don't think like that!

346
00:28:31.510 --> 00:28:32.800
Mother...

347
00:28:32.800 --> 00:28:36.000
Reiju! Come here!

348
00:28:37.420 --> 00:28:39.230
How is your father doing?

349
00:28:40.050 --> 00:28:43.580
All he does is train us.
He never plays with us.

350
00:28:43.580 --> 00:28:48.570
He's just happy that Ichiji, Niji, and Yonji
seem to be fine soldiers.

351
00:28:50.560 --> 00:28:51.870
I see.

352
00:28:51.870 --> 00:28:53.340
What is that?

353
00:28:53.340 --> 00:28:57.500
Sanji cooked it for me!

354
00:28:57.500 --> 00:28:59.130
Sanji did?

355
00:29:01.880 --> 00:29:08.130
Can you guess what Sanji told me today?

356
00:29:09.120 --> 00:29:12.220
He said, "Get well soon."

357
00:29:13.700 --> 00:29:15.990
He's the sweetest boy in the world!

358
00:29:18.350 --> 00:29:21.520
What are you doing here?

359
00:29:21.520 --> 00:29:23.060
Father...

360
00:29:27.050 --> 00:29:31.990
This compassion to lay flowers
for the dead is useless to you!

361
00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:47.710
Stop crying!

362
00:29:49.860 --> 00:29:51.510
Coward!

363
00:29:51.510 --> 00:29:53.200
Crybaby!

364
00:29:56.870 --> 00:29:57.960
Let's go.

365
00:29:59.750 --> 00:30:01.600
You too. Come on.

366
00:30:03.080 --> 00:30:04.310
Yes, sir.

367
00:30:07.380 --> 00:30:11.370
But our father's beliefs
were the total opposite of our mother's,

368
00:30:12.090 --> 00:30:15.270
and he never accepted you for who you were.

369
00:30:18.870 --> 00:30:24.400
He blamed you for everything that happened,
and mistreated you accordingly.

370
00:30:24.910 --> 00:30:27.720
Never cook again!

371
00:30:27.720 --> 00:30:31.380
What are you doing?! Fight back!

372
00:30:34.320 --> 00:30:37.270
Sanji is a worthless failure!

373
00:30:37.270 --> 00:30:39.710
Failure! Failure!

374
00:30:50.830 --> 00:30:53.830
Run!

375
00:30:53.830 --> 00:30:56.200
Don't look back!

376
00:30:56.200 --> 00:31:03.420
Even though our mother is no longer with us,
her grace is still there inside of you.

377
00:31:03.420 --> 00:31:07.420
There's no way that you're a failure.

378
00:31:07.420 --> 00:31:11.270
Our mother protected her child
at the risk of her own life,

379
00:31:11.270 --> 00:31:14.670
and he was born with the spark of humanity.

380
00:31:14.670 --> 00:31:18.600
That child is you, Sanji.

381
00:31:18.600 --> 00:31:23.690
That's why you're kinder than anyone else!

382
00:31:31.060 --> 00:31:33.110
Look for Straw Hat!

383
00:31:33.110 --> 00:31:34.780
Which way did he go?!

384
00:31:34.780 --> 00:31:38.950
He escaped from the underground Prisoner Library
and passed through the first floor already!

385
00:31:38.950 --> 00:31:42.120
Everyone, go to the second floor!

386
00:31:41.290 --> 00:31:42.120
Yes, sir!

387
00:31:46.080 --> 00:31:48.710
Sanji!

388
00:31:46.200 --> 00:31:48.710
<b>Whole Cake Chateau 2nd Floor</b>

389
00:31:49.080 --> 00:31:53.090
<b>Treasure Repository Entryway</b>

390
00:31:50.370 --> 00:31:53.090
What?! Another problem?

391
00:31:53.090 --> 00:31:56.670
Yes, ma'am.
Boss Jinbe is in the castle and...

392
00:31:56.670 --> 00:31:58.520
He's not rebelling, is he?

393
00:31:58.520 --> 00:32:01.720
Alright. Send this message to all soldiers.

394
00:32:01.720 --> 00:32:03.220
Okay.

395
00:32:06.930 --> 00:32:10.640
Tomorrow's plan is
Mama's long-awaited dream.

396
00:32:10.640 --> 00:32:11.310
Y-Yes.

397
00:32:11.310 --> 00:32:14.190
What will happen if we fail?

398
00:32:13.610 --> 00:32:14.190
What?

399
00:32:14.190 --> 00:32:18.260
In the worst-case scenario, what'll happen?

400
00:32:25.700 --> 00:32:28.730
I-I don't want to think about it!

401
00:32:28.730 --> 00:32:30.250
Me neither.

402
00:32:30.250 --> 00:32:35.030
If we bring any more problems
to Mama in her current mood,

403
00:32:35.030 --> 00:32:37.300
it'll affect tomorrow's mission.

404
00:32:37.300 --> 00:32:39.470
You're right!

405
00:32:39.470 --> 00:32:41.500
Then what shall we do?

406
00:32:42.380 --> 00:32:46.230
A-Are you... telling me to lie–

407
00:32:46.230 --> 00:32:48.790
If you lie to Mama, you'll be executed.

408
00:32:48.790 --> 00:32:51.130
F-Forgive me!

409
00:32:51.130 --> 00:32:56.490
If there isn't a problem,
we don't need to tell her anything.

410
00:32:56.490 --> 00:32:58.010
Don't you agree?

411
00:32:58.010 --> 00:33:00.440
Y-Yes, I agree!

412
00:33:02.480 --> 00:33:04.030
We're on the fourth floor.

413
00:33:04.030 --> 00:33:06.980
Block all the paths up to this floor!

414
00:33:06.980 --> 00:33:09.700
Handle everything on the lower levels.

415
00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:12.400
And get the situation under control immediately!

416
00:33:12.400 --> 00:33:15.120
Yes, ma'am. Understood!

417
00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:19.340
In that case, it's easier to kill them
than to capture them!

418
00:33:19.340 --> 00:33:23.130
That's fine. You have my permission!

419
00:33:22.390 --> 00:33:23.130
Yes, ma'am!

420
00:33:23.130 --> 00:33:27.100
Where's Sanji?!

421
00:33:32.570 --> 00:33:35.280
I'm asking where he is!

422
00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:39.490
Why are you still thinking?

423
00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:42.930
You already have your answer.

424
00:33:43.610 --> 00:33:46.750
Abandon Germa and run away, Sanji.

425
00:33:46.750 --> 00:33:51.740
Germa clings to glories from the past
and stands for nothing but destruction.

426
00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:54.970
The world doesn't need us.

427
00:33:54.970 --> 00:33:58.760
All Big Mom wants is our
advanced technology.

428
00:33:59.340 --> 00:34:03.890
I doubt she has any interest
in the life of your mentor.

429
00:34:05.100 --> 00:34:10.680
Father and our brothers are the ones who are
threatening to take that seafaring restaurant hostage,

430
00:34:10.680 --> 00:34:11.980
and they'll be dead tomorrow.

431
00:34:12.520 --> 00:34:17.110
It's exactly what we deserve,
since we're nothing but a band of murderers.

432
00:34:17.610 --> 00:34:22.870
My grudge is with them,
but why do you have to die too?!

433
00:34:23.570 --> 00:34:26.440
I still have my emotions,

434
00:34:26.440 --> 00:34:31.530
but I'm still a modified being
that cannot disobey Father's orders.

435
00:34:32.410 --> 00:34:34.340
My hands are stained with blood, too.

436
00:34:34.960 --> 00:34:36.800
I deserve death.

437
00:34:38.800 --> 00:34:42.130
I forgot to mention it, but those bracelets...

438
00:34:43.600 --> 00:34:47.680
They won't explode on you.
I swapped them out for ordinary ones.

439
00:34:49.870 --> 00:34:54.070
So what else is keeping you here?

440
00:34:55.900 --> 00:34:58.450
Get your act together, Sanji!

441
00:35:01.870 --> 00:35:03.990
Outta my way!

442
00:35:05.130 --> 00:35:07.910
Think about what's important to you!

443
00:35:08.470 --> 00:35:10.750
What's important to me?

444
00:35:10.750 --> 00:35:13.640
Stop, Straw Hat!

445
00:35:19.470 --> 00:35:22.250
Join my pirate crew!

446
00:35:22.250 --> 00:35:24.670
Be the cook on my pirate ship!

447
00:35:24.670 --> 00:35:27.520
Where are you?!

448
00:35:30.100 --> 00:35:34.460
You're a good cook,
so let's be pirates together!

449
00:35:34.810 --> 00:35:37.110
You'll never be able to meet...

450
00:35:37.730 --> 00:35:40.150
good friends...

451
00:35:40.150 --> 00:35:42.080
like them again!

452
00:35:44.580 --> 00:35:46.520
Outta my way!

453
00:35:46.520 --> 00:35:49.110
Sanji!
